In this article, the President of the United States congratulates the Sikh community on the anniversary of the birth of Guru Nanak Dev Ji, the first Sikh Guru. The President acknowledges Guru Nanak's teachings of equality, diversity, compassion, and tolerance, which have become the core principles of Sikhism. The President also recognizes the contributions of the Sikh American community in embodying these values and enriching the United States.